The paper uses data analysis to investigate how environmental changes affect individuals' musical preferences, which involves social and cultural factors. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also analyzes comprehensive data on over 16 million users on Spotify, which involves data mining and machine learning, making cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) another likely category. Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of adolescence on lifelong musical tastes, which involves psychological and cognitive factors, making cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) possible categories. Finally, the paper discusses the impact of geographic relocation, which involves geographical and spatial factors, making cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy) a possible category as well.
